tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE CustomerFeedback (
    feedback_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT,
    product_id INT,
    feedback_text TEXT,
    rating INT,
    feedback_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE customer_feedback (
    feedback_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT,
    product_id INT,
    rating INT,
    feedback_text TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE product_reviews (
    review_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INT,
    customer_id INT,
    review_text TEXT,
    rating INT
);

CREATE TABLE feedback_reviews (
  feedback_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  customer_id INT,
  review_text TEXT,
  rating INT,
  created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE customers (
  customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  customer_name VARCHAR(50),
  email VARCHAR(100),
  registration_date DATE,
  city VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE products (
  product_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  product_name VARCHAR(50),
  category VARCHAR(50),
  price DECIMAL,
  description TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE feedback_analysis (
  analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  feedback_id INT,
  sentiment_score DECIMAL,
  analysis_date DATE,
  suggestion TEXT
);
CREATE TABLE Feedback (feedback_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, feedback_text TEXT, rating INT, date_submitted DATE)
CREATE TABLE Customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name TEXT, email TEXT, phone_number TEXT, date_joined DATE)
CREATE TABLE Products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name TEXT, description TEXT, price DECIMAL(10,2))
CREATE TABLE Reviews (review_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_id INT, customer_id INT, review_text TEXT, rating INT, date_posted DATE)
CREATE TABLE Services (service_id INT PRIMARY KEY, service_name TEXT, description TEXT, price DECIMAL(10,2))
